  "texts": [
    "For nodule classification, the network exhibits a similar attention pattern for true positive cases (Fig. 6a) and false positive cases (Fig.",
    "AG-1 surveys the nodule and the microenvironment, AG-2 removes the attention on the nodule and surveys the surrounding microenvironment, and CAM at the last layer shifts the attention back to the nodule parenchyma.",
    "For true negative cases (Fig. 6c) and false negative cases (Fig.",
    "6d), another attention pattern is observed.",
    "The network attention starts with AG-1 the nodule and the microenvironment."
  ]
}